name: Marketo
description: Add a Marketo Instance to connect your existing Marketo account to the Marketing Hub, allowing you to manage accounts, campaigns, contacts, leads etc. across multiple Marketing Elements. You will need your Marketo account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an Marketo account, you can create one at Marketo Signup

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Companies Enabled
configuration.description: Set to true if the role has permission to operate on Companies

configuration.name: Opportunities Enabled
configuration.description: Set to true if the role has permission to operate on Opportunities

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Partition Name
configuration.description: Partition Name. Leave blank to use default partition

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Find the activities in Marketo, using the given, optional CEQL search expression. Lead Activity ID is required, and can be retrieved through GET /activityType. For more information: http://developers.marketo.com/documentation/rest/get-lead-activities/

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for activities for activityTypeIds 12 and 13, the search expression will be where=activityTypeIds in (12, 13) . activityTypeIds and fromDate are required parameter to search activities, the activities are returned in a paginated fashion. There is a maximum limit of 10 activityTypeIds that you can query at a time.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The token or link for getting the next page. This type of paging is a cursor based paging. Where you have to start at the beginning and traverse the result set.

resources.description: Create a new activity in Marketo associated to given lead records. More information can be found here: http://developers.marketo.com/rest-api/endpoint-reference/lead-database-endpoint-reference/#!/Activities/addCustomActivityUsingPOST

parameters.name: customActivity
parameters.description:
The Custom Activity object to be created.
With the exception of the 'id' field, the required fields indicated in the Your Custom Activity model that you have defined at Marketo. This is a Non Standard API that requires the Cumtom Activity be defined by Marketo Support before you can use this api.

resources.description: Get a list of all activity types
Upload a file of objects to be bulk uploaded to Marketo.

parameters.name: Elements-Async-Callback-Url
parameters.description: The Url to send the notification to when the Job is completed

parameters.name: objectName
parameters.description: The name of the object for which data needs to be uploaded.

parameters.name: metaData
parameters.description: JSON MetaData that contains the details needed for upload, ex: {"listId" : <listId resource>, "primaryKeyName":"id", "format": <json/csv>}. Where listId is the id of the list to upload contacts to example: {"listId":"1014","action":"upsert","primaryKeyName":"id"}  If the Upload format is JSON pass metadata as {"format":"json"}.

parameters.name: file
parameters.description: The file of objects to bulk load.

resources.description: Find campaigns in Marketo, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all campaigns whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name in '%data%'. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 200 records will be returned. More information can be found here: http://developers.marketo.com/documentation/rest/get-multiple-campaigns/

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: Only the 'in' clause is support for the allowed variables eg 'id in (1,2,3) and name in ('Test','EmailCampaign')'

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The token or link for getting the next page. This type of paging is a cursor based paging. Where you have to start at the beginning and traverse the result set.

Campaign.description: A campaign object. With the exception of the 'id' field, the required fields indicated are those required to create a new campaign. For other campaign operations, the required fields will be a subset of these fields. There will be other fields returned with a Campaign, which are not all described here.

resources.description: Trigger a campaign with for the given contacts.  Pass in an array of contact ids.

parameters.name: campaignId
parameters.description: The ID of the campaign, to which contacts need to be added.

parameters.name: campaignContacts
parameters.description: The contact object which needs to be added to the campaign. This object has a different set of attributes than the Contact model object.

CampaignContact.description: A existing contact object in a campaign.

resources.description: Retrieve a campaign associated with a given ID from Marketo.  Specifying a campaign associated with a given ID that does not exist will result in an error response.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the campaign to retrieve from Marketo.

Campaign.description: A campaign object. With the exception of the 'id' field, the required fields indicated are those required to create a new campaign. For other campaign operations, the required fields will be a subset of these fields. There will be other fields returned with a Campaign, which are not all described here.

resources.description: Find Contact Changes

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: You need to supply a sinceDate eg sinceDate= '2016-01-01T13:20:22Z' and listId = 1234. listId is optional.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: You can supply a comma delimited list of fields.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of items returned in a query. Defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The token or link for getting the next page. This type of paging is a cursor based paging. Where you have to start at the beginning and traverse the result set.

resources.description: Find companies in the Marketo using a provided CEQL search expression. Marketo API documentation can be found here: http://developers.marketo.com/documentation/company-api/get-companies/

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Marketo requires a query parameter. Valid search fields are id, and standard fields Ex. id in(1,2,35, 76). More information can be found at http://developers.marketo.com/documentation/company-api/get-companies/

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of items returned in a query. Defaults to 100 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The token or link for getting the next page. This type of paging is a cursor based paging. Where you have to start at the beginning and traverse the result set.

resources.description: Update the company in Marketo associated with the given ID.
